# Read project docs first

For any non-trivial task (behavior, architecture, text/font, build, or repo layout):

1. Read **`docs/prd.md`** (product requirements: scope, Czech/font constraints, acceptance criteria). Same document as **`PRD.md`** / **`prd.md`** on typical filesystems.
2. Read **`docs/CODEMAP.md`** to see which `src/pokyd_*.c` fragment owns the feature and where symbols are declared (`src/pokyd.h`).

Then follow **`AGENTS.md`** and the fragment-specific rules under `.cursor/rules/pokyd-*.mdc` as applicable.
